{"title": "Caught in the Bad Part of Town", "content": "In many cities, there is an acknowledged \"bad part of town\": a place where outsiders just don't go. This trope is what happens when characters who don't belong find themselves in this bad part of town.\n\nThis trope can play out in a number of different ways. In more hopeful works, the characters could discover that not everyone in The City Narrows is a bad person and learn a lesson about judging by appearances. In other works, the characters will face a nail biting adventure as they find their way out and back to more familiar ground. In Crime and Punishment Series, they might just end up dead.\n\nIn a military / warfare context, this can be lethally serious. As in the inhabitants of this side of town / this side of the front lines want to kill the character.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaughtInTheBadPartOfTown", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/LaytonMysteryDetectiveAgency", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BatmanNoMansLand", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/RobinSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Nightwing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BakerStreet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheLionKing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FinalFantasyTheSpiritsWithin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/LadyAndTheTramp", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AdventuresInBabysitting", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BehindEnemyLines", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JudgmentNight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AfterHours", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBigTease", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/JediAcademyTrilogy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HonorHarrington", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBonfireOfTheVanities", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSINY", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Arrow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ManuelSamuel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Persona3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Sorcery", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons", "